      "writtenOn": "2021-02-04T22:46:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not for this CL, but a future idea: it seems like an SkSL::Operator class that holds a Token::Kind and provides methods like getBinaryPrecedence and operatorName would be even better. Anyplace that stores a Token::Kind could switch to SkSL::Operator, and it would be basically free to make a temporary one from a Token.\n\nThat is...\n\n  Operators::IsAssignment(fMyToken)    --\u003e fMyOperator.isAssignment()\n\nor...\n\n  Operators::IsAssignment(myTempToken) --\u003e Operator(myTempToken).isAssignment()",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 9,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 9,
        "endChar": 22
      },
